#. <section class="sutta" id="an10.39"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an10.39:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.39:0.2"
msgid "4. Upālivagga"
msgstr "4. With Upāli"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.39:0.3"
msgid "39. Paṭhamaānandasutta"
msgstr "39. With Ānanda (1st)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.75"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an10.39:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā ānando yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā ānando "
"bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Venerable Ānanda went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, "
"and said to the Buddha:"

msgctxt "an10.39:1.2"
msgid "“‘saṅghabhedo saṅghabhedo’ti, bhante, vuccati."
msgstr "“Sir, they speak of ‘schism in the Saṅgha’."

msgctxt "an10.39:1.3"
msgid "Kittāvatā nu kho, bhante, saṅgho bhinno hotī”ti?"
msgstr "How is schism in the Saṅgha defined?”"

msgctxt "an10.39:1.4"
msgid ""
"“Idhānanda, bhikkhū adhammaṃ dhammoti dīpenti, dhammaṃ adhammoti dīpenti, "
"avinayaṃ vinayoti dīpenti … pe …"
msgstr ""
"“Ānanda, it’s when a mendicant explains what is not the teaching as the "
"teaching …"

msgctxt "an10.39:1.5"
msgid "paññattaṃ tathāgatena apaññattaṃ tathāgatenāti dīpenti."
msgstr ""
"and what was prescribed by the Realized One as not prescribed by the "
"Realized One."

msgctxt "an10.39:1.6"
msgid ""
"Te imehi dasahi vatthūhi avakassanti apakassanti āveni kammāni karonti āveni "
"pātimokkhaṃ uddisanti."
msgstr ""
"On these ten grounds they split off and go their own way. They perform legal "
"acts autonomously and recite the monastic code autonomously."

msgctxt "an10.39:1.7"
msgid "Ettāvatā kho, ānanda, saṅgho bhinno hotī”ti."
msgstr "That is how schism in the Saṅgha is defined.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an10.39:2.1"
msgid "“Samaggaṃ pana, bhante, saṅghaṃ bhinditvā kiṃ so pasavatī”ti?"
msgstr ""
"“But sir, what does someone who has caused a schism in a harmonious Saṅgha "
"bring upon themselves?”"

msgctxt "an10.39:2.2"
msgid "“Kappaṭṭhikaṃ, ānanda, kibbisaṃ pasavatī”ti."
msgstr "“They bring upon themselves evil that lasts for an eon.”"

msgctxt "an10.39:2.3"
msgid "“Kiṃ pana, bhante, kappaṭṭhikaṃ kibbisan”ti?"
msgstr "“But sir, what is the evil that lasts for an eon?”"

msgctxt "an10.39:2.4"
msgid "“Kappaṃ, ānanda, nirayamhi paccatīti—"
msgstr "“They burn in hell for an eon, Ānanda."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.76"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an10.39:3.1"
msgid "Āpāyiko nerayiko,"
msgstr "A schismatic remains for the eon"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an10.39:3.2"
msgid "Kappaṭṭho saṃghabhedako;"
msgstr "in a place of loss, in hell."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an10.39:3.3"
msgid "Vaggarato adhammaṭṭho,"
msgstr "Basing themselves in what is not the teaching,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an10.39:3.4"
msgid "Yogakkhemā padhaṃsati;"
msgstr "favoring factions, they destroy their sanctuary."

#. <br>
#. VAR: bhinditvā → bhetvāna (bj, s1-3, pts1) | bhitvāna (mr)
msgctxt "an10.39:3.5"
msgid "Saṃghaṃ samaggaṃ bhinditvā,"
msgstr "After causing schism in a harmonious Saṅgha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an10.39:3.6"
msgid "Kappaṃ nirayamhi paccatī”ti."
msgstr "they burn in hell for an eon.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.39:3.7"
msgid "Navamaṃ."
msgstr ""
